You can achieve it by using [Custom Data - Attaching Data Objects to Controls](https://help.sap.com/doc/saphelp_uiaddon20/2.05/en-US/91/f0c3ee6f4d1014b6dd926db0e91070/content.htm?no_cache=true)

To use custom data you need to use the following namespace for the respective attributes:

    myNamespace=&quot;http://schemas.sap.com/sapui5/extension/sap.ui.core.CustomData/1&quot;

**XML view**

In XML view you need to include the **namespace** also need to use `app:mySuperExtraData=&quot;CUSTTOM DATA&quot;` to attach custom data to the control.

    &lt;mvc:View xmlns:core=&quot;sap.ui.core&quot; xmlns:mvc=&quot;sap.ui.core.mvc&quot; xmlns=&quot;sap.ui.commons&quot; controllerName=&quot;my.own.controller&quot;
      xmlns:app=&quot;http://schemas.sap.com/sapui5/extension/sap.ui.core.CustomData/1&quot;&gt;
         &lt;Button text=&quot;Click&quot; app:mySuperExtraData=&quot;just great&quot;&gt;&lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;/mvc:View&gt;

**Use with Data Binding**

    &lt;mvc:View xmlns:core=&quot;sap.ui.core&quot; xmlns:mvc=&quot;sap.ui.core.mvc&quot; xmlns=&quot;sap.ui.commons&quot; controllerName=&quot;my.own.controller&quot; 
               xmlns:app=&quot;http://schemas.sap.com/sapui5/extension/sap.ui.core.CustomData/1&quot;&gt;
         &lt;Button text=&quot;Click&quot; app:coords=&quot;{data}&quot; press=&quot;alertCoordinates&quot;&gt;&lt;/Button&gt;
    &lt;/mvc:View&gt;

**JS view**

By using `data()` we can attach data objects to controls.

    myButton.data(&quot;myData&quot;, &quot;Hello&quot;);

**Retrieve custom data** 

    myButton.data(&quot;myData&quot;)

