Then this is not a use case for asynchronous programming. Your requirement is that this is synchronous.

That is especially so since you said that `MyMethod1`/`MyMethod2`/`MyMethod3` are not asynchronous methods. If they were, that would be a [totally different thing][1]. But since they aren&#39;t, I don&#39;t see any value in trying to use `async` and `await` here.

